The paper discusses Runtime Monitoring, which is a technique used in software engineering to verify the correctness of a software system. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses different types of monitoring methodologies and instrumentation techniques, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL), logic (cs.LO), and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the interactions of the software system with external entities, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
